post_text:
Cardinal Nation!

Pre-School classes resume on Tuesday, January 8, 2019. Please have a Happy Holiday Season!

Carrie Gosch ELC will host a Make and Take for parents on January 7, 2019 from 10:00 until 11:00.

Top 20 ii and Carrie Gosch ELC will begin Ballet class at 2:30 PM on January 15 and Tap Dance class at 2:30 PM on January 17. Please send forms and fees to Carrie Gosch by Wednesday, January 9, 2019 if interested. Classes will be filled on a first come, first served basis.

Have a Happy New Year Everyone!

post_text:
Take a look at Ms. Michelle Horst and her "We The People" class as they simulate a Congressional hearing in front of a panel of judges.

https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=2ctpu9CdZfc&t=3s

The "We The People" course at East Chicago Central High School is a course centered around the Constitution and other Founding Era documents. The students learn about their rights and responsibilities to a degree greater than normal social studies classes. They also learn the most important lesson: Our government belongs to us.

Learn more about our High School and our other wonderful schools at scec.k12.in.us

post_text:
Cardinal Nation!

Our page is back up and running. üòÅ

We will post regularly to keep our parents, students, staff, former students, and any other individuals informed on anything SCEC related. Feel free to share our page to others. Also, if you have any general questions, please visit our homepage at scec.k12.in.us. Any other questions, please send them to askcardinalnation@ecps.org. We will get back to you in a timely manner.

Have a great weekend Cardinals!
